{"parse":{"title":"The Le Cheile Schools Trust","pageid":56846772,"revid":849511640,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>The Le Ch\u00e9ile Schools Trust</b> is a charitable trust which manages around 60 schools in <a href=\"/wiki/Republic_of_Ireland\" title=\"Republic of Ireland\">Ireland</a> on behalf of fourteen Roman Catholic religious congregations. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Mission_and_establishment\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Mission and establishment</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Operations\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Operations</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Schools\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Schools</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Congregations_participating_in_Le_Cheile\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Congregations participating in Le Cheile</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Le_Cheile_Schools_Trust&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The formation of the trust was agreed in 2004<sup id=\"cite_ref-IT_LeCheile_plans_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-IT_LeCheile_plans-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>, and fully enacted over the following years, with the body established as a company limited by guarantee in 2008.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Mission_and_establishment\">Mission and establishment</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Le_Cheile_Schools_Trust&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Mission and establishment\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Its mission is to maintain and promote the <a href=\"/wiki/Catholic\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Catholic\">Catholic</a> ethos of these schools, and develop new schools where the need arises. \n</p><p>Originally set up by twelve Roman Catholic religious congregations, fourteen congregations are involved as of 2018, with their schools entrusted to Le Cheile.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> 59 voluntary and 7 community schools are managed by the trust. \nIn 2013 the Ursuline College joined the trust.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> In 2009 the <a href=\"/wiki/Sisters_of_St._Joseph_of_Cluny\" title=\"Sisters of St. Joseph of Cluny\">Sisters of St. Joseph of Cluny</a> joined Le Cheile.\n</p><p>In September 2014, in <a href=\"/wiki/Tyrellstown\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tyrellstown\">Tyrellstown</a>, Le Cheile opened the first Catholic secondary school in 30 years in Ireland.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Operations\">Operations</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Le_Cheile_Schools_Trust&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Operations\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Trust's administration office is based in the Jesuit complex at Milltown Park, Dublin, and the trust produces a newsletter called <i>Le Cheile Update</i>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Schools\">Schools</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Le_Cheile_Schools_Trust&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Schools\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A partial list of the schools within the Trust follows:\n</p>\n<ul><li>St. Angela's College, Cork</li>\n<li>Mount Sackville Secondary School, Chapelizod, Dublin (Sisters of St Joseph of Cluny)</li>\n<li>Maryfield College, Dublin</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Muckross_Park_College\" title=\"Muckross Park College\">Muckross Park College</a>, Dublin</li>\n<li>Our Lady's School, Templeogue, Dublin<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>St. Wolstan's Community School, Celbridge, Kildare</li>\n<li>Dominican College, Galway</li>\n<li>Scoil \u00cdde, Salthill, Galway</li>\n<li>Scoil Pol, Kilfinane, Co. Limerick</li>\n<li>Ursuline College, Sligo (Ursuline Sisters)</li>\n<li>Le Cheile Secondary School, Tyrrelstown, Dublin<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Our Lady\u2019s Grove, Goatstown, Dublin 14</li>\n<li>St. Louis Infant School, Rathmines, Dublin 6</li>\n<li>St. Louis Primary School, Rathmines, Dublin 6</li>\n<li>Mother of Divine Grace, Primary School, Ballygall, Glasnevin, Dublin 11 (Holy Faith Sisters)</li>\n<li>St. Paul\u2019s Senior Primary School, Dublin 12</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Congregations_participating_in_Le_Cheile\">Congregations participating in Le Cheile</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Le_Cheile_Schools_Trust&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Congregations participating in Le Cheile\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/De_La_Salle_Brothers\" title=\"De La Salle Brothers\">De La Salle Brothers</a></li>\n<li>Dominican Sisters</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Faithful_Companions_of_Jesus\" title=\"Faithful Companions of Jesus\">Faithful Companions of Jesus</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Patrician_Brothers\" title=\"Patrician Brothers\">Patrician Brothers</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Poor_Servants_of_the_Mother_of_God\" title=\"Poor Servants of the Mother of God\">Poor Servants of the Mother of God</a></li>\n<li>Religious of Christian Education</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Religious_of_Jesus_and_Mary\" title=\"Religious of Jesus and Mary\">Religious of Jesus and Mary</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Sisters_of_Charity_of_St._Paul\" title=\"Sisters of Charity of St. Paul\">Sisters of Charity of St. Paul</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Sisters_of_St._Louis\" title=\"Sisters of St. Louis\">Sisters of St. Louis</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Sisters_of_the_Cross_and_Passion\" title=\"Sisters of the Cross and Passion\">Sisters of the Cross and Passion</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Sisters_of_St._Joseph_of_Cluny\" title=\"Sisters of St. Joseph of Cluny\">Sisters of St. Joseph of Cluny</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Society_of_the_Holy_Child_Jesus\" title=\"Society of the Holy Child Jesus\">Society of the Holy Child Jesus</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Sisters_of_the_Holy_Faith\" title=\"Sisters of the Holy Faith\">Sisters of the Holy Faith</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Ursulines\" title=\"Ursulines\">Ursuline Sisters</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Le_Cheile_Schools_Trust&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-IT_LeCheile_plans-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-IT_LeCheile_plans_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Downes, John. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.irishtimes.com/news/orders-to-form-joint-trust-to-run-their-schools-1.1308733\">\"Orders to form joint trust to run their schools\"</a>. <i>The Irish Times</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2004-04-20</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Irish+Times&amp;rft.atitle=Orders+to+form+joint+trust+to+run+their+schools&amp;rft.aulast=Downes&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irishtimes.com%2Fnews%2Forders-to-form-joint-trust-to-run-their-schools-1.1308733&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Le+Cheile+Schools+Trust\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.muckrossparkcollege.com/index.php/about-us/le-cheile-trust\">Le Cheile Trust</a> Muckross Park College</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external 